IO
==

Overview
--------
`io/` contains only persistence classes and low-level private helper code.

The classes form a simple chain:

```text
input ROOT files
    |
    v
InputPartitionIO
    |
    v
SampleIO
    |
    v
DatasetIO
    |
    v
EventListIO
```

More concretely:

```text
InputPartitionIO --scans--> one input file list / partition
SampleIO         --builds--> one sample container from one or more partitions
SampleIO         --exports-> DatasetIO::Sample metadata
DatasetIO        --holds--> many named samples and their metadata
EventListIO      --writes-> selected event trees, subrun trees, and cache payloads
EventListIO      --serves-> downstream plotting, systematics, and ad hoc analysis
```

Class notes
-----------
`InputPartitionIO`
  Small record for one partition of input ROOT files. It scans subruns, POT,
  and event counts and can write or read that partition summary.

`SampleIO`
  Builds a sample-level container from one or more `InputPartitionIO`
  partitions. It is the bridge between raw input lists and `DatasetIO::Sample`
  metadata.

`DatasetIO`
  Persistent collection of named samples. It stores sample metadata and sample
  provenance, but not selected event trees.

`EventListIO`
  Persistent analysis-ready output. It stores copied selected event trees,
  subrun trees, sample metadata, and persisted systematics cache payloads.
  Downstream code should usually open `EventListIO` and stay on that surface.

Private material
----------------
`bits/`
  Private helper code and schema notes used by `io/` itself.

`bits/NTUPLE`
  Reference for the upstream input ntuple schema.

`bits/DERIVED`
  Reference for framework-owned derived columns and persisted `EventListIO`
  structure.
